title: Get a birthday or anniversary message from the King

heading_context: Get a birthday or anniversary message from the King
If the person gets a State Pension or other benefit and lives in the UK
chunks.html_content:
You can get a free birthday or anniversary message from the King and the Queen Consort for a British national.

You can get a message for someone’s:

  • 100th birthday
  • 105th birthday
  • birthday each year following their 105th

You do not need to apply for a birthday message.

This will be sent using the name and address on the person’s State Pension or other benefit record.

To update a State Pension record, contact the Pension Service.

To update any other benefit record, report a change in circumstances.

heading_context: Get a birthday or anniversary message from the King
If the person does not get a State Pension or other benefit or does not live in the UK
chunks.html_content:
You need to apply for a message. You can apply:

  • no earlier than 5 weeks before the birthday date
  • up to 6 months after for a belated message

Apply for a birthday message online.

Find out more, including how to apply by post, on the Royal website.

heading_context: Get a birthday or anniversary message from the King
If you do not have a copy of the marriage certificate and the couple got married in England or Wales
chunks.html_content:
You can get a message for a couple’s:

  • 60th (diamond) anniversary
  • 65th anniversary
  • 70th (platinum) anniversary
  • anniversary each year following their 70th

You can apply:

  • no earlier than 5 weeks before the anniversary date if you apply online, or 3 weeks before if you apply by post
  • up to 6 months after for a belated message

You’ll need to send a copy of the couple’s marriage certificate when you apply.

Apply for an anniversary message online.

Find out more, including how to apply by post, on the Royal website.

Call the General Register Office to apply 8 weeks before the anniversary.

You’ll need:

  • the names of the couple
  • their current address
  • the date and place of the marriage

The General Register Office will confirm the details and request the anniversary message for you.

heading_context: Get a birthday or anniversary message from the King
If the person lives in Australia, Canada or New Zealand
chunks.html_content: You must apply directly to the Governor-General. For contact details call the Anniversaries Office.
